item.title: [PI] Quest Tab Cleared And Auto Update
item.dc:creator: @n10si_t n10si t
item.description:
@n10si_t wrote:

[quote=“Uncalled, post:10, topic:525389”][quote author=n10si t link=topic=644133.msg4335405#msg4335405 date=1374265187]

This would probably make your server crash, or at least unplayable due to lag.

This is far from true, however cramming code into your ‘process’ method is a very bad idea. That’s now just one more thing your server needs to execute every 500 - 600 m/s. Updating text via the walking packet or upon login is a better idea.

the sendFrame126 method is notorious for causing extreme lag, and running it that many times that often is just horrendous. I’m not really trying to prove my point here, but if you can, download a PI and try it. You’ll be surprised
[/quote]Not entirely. It depends on the source, of course, how much lag it will cause. But for a lot of sources, it doesn’t even come close to crashing your server or causing an immense amount of latency. At least with all the sources I’ve used with it.[/quote]

A standard PI, mind you. I’m well aware that there are sources (including yours :P) that do a much better job at handling that sort of thing.

I’ve done it before, in the quest tab using process and writing on a book interface (not in process)
